body:
Thank you for your pull request. Before we can look at your contribution, we need to ensure all contributors are covered by a Contributor License Agreement.

After the following items are addressed, please respond with a new comment here, and the automated system will re-verify.

* User @jakobr-google isn't covered by a CLA. They will need to complete the form at https://identity.linuxfoundation.org/projects/cncf

_Regards,
CLA GitHub bot_

- It looks like that all cloud_to_cloud interop tests (dart vs all other languages) are passing: https://sponge.corp.google.com/target?id=73149d82-d16c-48c0-b31d-534c4a417029&target=github/grpc&searchFor=&show=ALL&sortBy=STATUS

- some interop_to_prod tests are failing (it looks like it's the cloud_to_prod_auth tests: `compute_engine_creds`, `per_rpc_creds`, `oauth2_auth_token` and `jwt_token_creds`). Is the auth layer implemented in grpc-dart?
https://sponge.corp.google.com/target?id=2971401b-1742-44d4-a6a8-dda703505047&target=grpc/ubuntu/pull_request/grpc_interop_toprod&searchFor=&show=ALL&sortBy=STATUS

- you need to sign the CNCF CLA so the cla check bot is happy.
I've signed up with CNCF. Dart gRPC does have auth support, but I hadn't implemented the interop tests for it yet. I'll wire them up early next week when I'm back from DartConf.

I re-ran the tests, and most auth tests have indeed been fixed by https://github.com/dart-lang/grpc-dart/pull/55.

The only remaining test is now `compute_engine_creds`

```

https://sponge.corp.google.com/target?id=1e713124-8173-4afb-b512-5f4cec4e0c50&target=github/grpc&searchFor=&show=ALL&sortBy=STATUS
I think I've fixed the compute_engine_creds test. Could you kick off a new run to verify, please?

Its failing with an unrelated node problem:
```

which prevents the tests from running. I'm looking into this.

```
Corrupt JSON data (indicates timeout or crash): 
    bm_fullstack_streaming_pump.BM_PumpStreamServerToClient_MinSockPair__0.opt.old: 1


[microbenchmarks] No significant performance differences
```

To work around the Node.js docker build problem, I've setup a separate PR just to test this:
https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/14352

and the results show that `compute_engine_creds` is now passing.

https://sponge.corp.google.com/target?id=88f4fd4b-d51f-47fb-b9e7-1947e411ca30&target=github/grpc&searchFor=&show=ALL&sortBy=STATUS

Thanks for the fix!

I'm now happy with the state of interop tests, so here are the next steps:
- I'll initiate the transition to grpc/grpc-dart internally (see e-mail).
- Once the repository has been transitioned, we can adjust this PR to point to the new repository and merge it (there's no point of merging now, then transitioning which would break everything and fixing in a separate PR)
